Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel). Pop the wedges on a large, low sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle
with @oil{} and sprinkle over half the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once
your oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm
sized chunks. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(thinly sliced). Peel the
@garlic cloves{2} and pop into a square of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and
scrunch to enclose it. Roast on the same baking tray as the wedges until soft,
~{10-12%minutes}. Coarsely grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Chop the @British Honey Mustard sausages{4} into bite sized pieces (about 2cm).
Pop them in a large #bowl{} with the chopped pepper, remaining @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}
and half of the @BBQ sauce{64%g}. Mix it all together with your hands to coat
evenly. Thread the pepper and sausage chunks onto the #bamboo skewers{1} alternating
between the two.

> You are aiming for two skewers per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop the skewers onto the lined baking tray and bake on the top shelf of your
oven until cooked, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.
> Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Once the roasted garlic has cooled, crush it with the back of a #fork{} until
you have a smooth paste and pop into a bowl with the @mayonnaise{1} and
@coleslaw mix{120%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well to combine.
Set aside. Once everything has 5 mins left, evenly sprinkle over the grated
Cheddar and spring onion on the wedges and return to the oven to cook until the
cheese is melted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once everything is cooked, pop 2 skewers per person onto your plates. Share the
cheesy wedges along side and finish with the roasted garlic slaw and a dollop of
leftover bbq sauce. Enjoy!